Package: systemPipeCLIPseq
Title: High-throughput sequencing of RNA isolated by crosslinking immunoprecipitation (CLIP-Seq) analysis pipeline
Version: 0.9.0
Date: 2020-02-22
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Daniela", family = "Cassol", role = c("aut", "cre"), email="danielac@ucr.edu"), 
    person(given = "Thomas", family = "Girke", role = c("aut")))
Description: This package provides a pre-configured workflow and reporting template for CLIP-seq analysis.
biocViews: Genetics, Infrastructure, DataImport, Sequencing, RNASeq, RiboSeq, ChIPSeq, MethylSeq, CLIP-seq, SNP, GeneExpression, Coverage, GeneSetEnrichment, Alignment, QualityControl, ImmunoOncology
Imports: systemPipeR (>= 1.21.0), systemPipeRdata (>= 1.15.0)
Suggests: BiocStyle, knitr, rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
SystemRequirements: systemPipeCLIPseq can be used to run external 
        command-line software (e.g. short read aligners), but the 
        corresponding tool needs to be installed on a system.  
License: Artistic-2.0
URL: http://girke.bioinformatics.ucr.edu/systemPipeR/, https://github.com/systemPipeR/systemPipeCLIPseq
